## Google Cloud Security
This Repository contains lab activities documented from both the Google cybersecurity and Cloud security professional program on coursera. Through the Google Cybersecurity Professional Certificate on Coursera, I have developed strong foundational and practical cybersecurity skills through extensive hands-on labs and real-world security simulations. The program exposed me to critical areas of cybersecurity including threat detection, network security, incident response, vulnerability management, security operations, Linux, SQL, Python, SIEM tools, and security auditing. These practical activities strengthened my ability to analyze security events, investigate vulnerabilities, and apply defensive security measures in realistic environments. The laboratory exercises throughout the program were highly intensive and problem-solving oriented, requiring deep attention to detail, analytical reasoning, and the ability to work through complex cybersecurity scenarios under pressure. Many of the labs simulated real industry workflows involving log analysis, risk assessment, access control, packet inspection, and system hardening, helping me gain confidence with tools and techniques used by cybersecurity professionals today.


Through the Google Cloud Cybersecurity Professional Certificate on Coursera, I gained practical experience in cloud security operations, threat management, risk assessment, incident response, and security monitoring through immersive hands-on laboratory activities and cloud-based security simulations. The program provided real-world exposure to Google Cloud technologies and cybersecurity workflows, allowing me to build technical skills that align with modern cloud security and SOC environments. Throughout the program, I worked with tools and services such as Google Cloud Platform, Cloud Shell, Security Command Center, Cloud Logging, IAM, Cloud Storage, firewalls, and monitoring systems. The labs were highly intensive and detail-oriented, requiring analytical thinking, troubleshooting, access control configuration, vulnerability assessment, incident investigation, and cloud security implementation under realistic scenarios. These activities strengthened my ability to identify threats, secure cloud infrastructure, and apply cybersecurity best practices in dynamic environments.  

